00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:03,714
Did you know that these are the US Cardinals who will help elect the next Pope?

2
00:00:04,415 --> 00:00:10,060
With 10 eligible voters, America has the second highest number of electors, behind Italy’s 17.

3
00:00:10,742 --> 00:00:17,068
On March 12, these Cardinals will gather in the Vatican’s Sistine Chapel for the conclave to pick Pope Francis’ successor.

4
00:00:17,689 --> 00:00:29,481
This event is significant because the Pope holds immense spiritual and political power within the Catholic Church, influencing beliefs and actions of over a billion people worldwide.

5
00:00:29,460 --> 00:00:32,189
So, who are these American electors?

6
00:00:32,851 --> 00:00:40,274
They include Cardinal Blaise Cupich, Archbishop of Chicago, and Cardinal Joseph Tobin, Archbishop of Newark, among others.

